modules.description: Provides functions to allocate, map, and manipulate I/O memory pages, including reading from and writing to page-aligned buffers. Operates on Cstruct.t values, enabling direct access to memory without data duplication. Used in low-level system programming for direct device communication and memory-mapped I/O operations.

Provides operations for handling page-level I/O with a dummy implementation, focusing on integer-based page identifiers. Works with low-level page indices and simulation-specific data structures. Used to simulate page access patterns in virtualized environments without actual hardware interaction.
